cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the application of Deep Q-Learning Networks to multiagent environments, which falls under the category of reinforcement learning and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the emergence of competitive and collaborative behaviors in multiagent systems, which falls under the category of multiagent systems and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI and cs.MA likely sub-categories as well. The paper also uses neural networks to learn and optimize strategies, which falls under the category of neural networks and computational neuroscience, making cs.NE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses the classic videogame Pong as a testbed, which involves image processing and computer vision, making cs.CV a possible sub-category.
